The RCCI value was taken as the mean over three climate change scenarios analyzed (high medium and low), and so is not directly comparable with what we should see. Regardless, in the Amazon region, this study found an increase in wet season precipitation (Nov-Apr) of 4.02{\%}; but this is compensated for by a decrease in dry season precipitation of 4.49{\%}. Central America sees a decrease of precipitation in both seasons. During the wet season here (May-Oct), the decrease is 9.44{\%}, and uring the dry season (Nov-Apr) the decrease is 17.34{\%}. So we could expect to see larger changes in GPP in Central American than in the Amazon.},
author = {Giorgi, F.},
