climate proxies to compare CGCM simulations and
proxy observations to address 20th-century trends
and assess remaining uncertainties in both proxies
and models. We model coral oxygen isotopic
composition (delta O-18) in a 23-site Indo-Pacific
network as a linear function of sea-surface
temperature (SST) and sea-surface salinity (SSS)
obtained from historical marine observations
(instrumental data) and a multimodel ensemble of
20th-century CGCM output. When driven with
instrumental data from 1958 to 1990, the forward
