fire, cool sea surface temperatures (SSTs) along the
California coast, and dune mobilization in the
western plains. This Medieval Climate Anomaly (MCA)
was followed by wetter conditions and warming
coastal SSTs during the transition into the "Little
Ice Age" (LIA). Proxy records from the tropical
