northwestern Pacific. The generally reversed SLP and
precipitation patterns during La Nina winters are
consistent only during the low NPO phase. Climatic
anomalies tend to be weak and spatially incoherent
during low NPO-El Nino and high NPO-La Nina
winters. These results suggest that confidence in
ENSO-based long-range climate forecasts for North
America should reflect interdecadal climatic
anomalies in the North Pacific.},
