indicates that several of the largest decadal-scale
SST variations at Rarotonga are coherent with SST
regime shifts in the North Pacific. This hemispheric
symmetry suggests that tropical forcing may be an
important factor in at least some of the decadal
variability observed in the Pacific Ocean.},
