behavior. To the extent that such modulation is
realistic, it could attach large uncertainties to
ENSO metrics diagnosed from centennial and shorter
records - with important implications for historical
and paleo records, climate projections, and model
assessment and intercomparison. Analysis of the wait
times between ENSO warm events suggests that such
slow modulation need not require multidecadal
memory; it can arise simply from Poisson statistics
