occurred in 1997. (The rapid succession of several
westerly wind bursts in early 1997 was a relatively
rare phenomenon.) In late 2001, conditions were
similar to those in 1996, which suggested a
relatively high probability of El Nino appearing in
2002. Whether the event will be weak or intense
depends on the random disturbances that materialize
during the year.},
