fingerprint of temporal and spatial `sign-switching'
responses uniquely predicted by twentieth century
climate trends. Among appropriate
long-term/large-scale/multi-species data sets, this
diagnostic fingerprint was found for 279
species. This suite of analyses generates `very high
confidence' (as laid down by the IPCC) that climate
change is already affecting living systems.},
