climate? Studies with an idealized ocean general
circulation model find that vertical diffusivity is
one of the critical parameters that affect the
relative strength of the two circulation components
and hence their response to a freshening. The
spatial structure of the freshening and imposed
meridional temperature gradients are other important
factors.},
